      • get

        public <T> T get(java.lang.String key,
                 T defaultValue)
        Description copied from interface: IPropertyContainer
        Reads a per-object user-defined property identified by a custom key, and returns the stored value if a value was assigned by calling IPropertyContainer.set(String, Type, Object) earlier. Properties are stored persistently if ValueProtection.NORMAL_PROTECTION or ValueProtection.READ_ONLY_PERSISTENT was used when calling IPropertyContainer.set(String, Type, Object) or temporarily. The latest (maybe volatile) state will be taken into account, depending on the call of IPropertyContainer.remove(String). If no value was assigned (the key is unknown), the defaultValue will be returned.
        Specified by:
        get in interface IPropertyContainer
        Parameters:
        key - property name (case insensitive)
        defaultValue - value to return if no property is set
        Returns:
        value associated with key if set, defaultValue otherwise
        See Also:
        IPropertyContainer.get(String, Object), IPropertyContainer.has(String), IPropertyContainer.remove(String)

      • get

        public <T> T get(java.lang.String key)
          throws IPropertyContainer.NoSuchPropertyException
        Description copied from interface: IPropertyContainer
        Reads a per-object user-defined property identified by a custom key, and returns the stored value if a value was assigned by calling IPropertyContainer.set(String, Type, Object) earlier. Properties are stored persistently such that an assignment will be alive as long as it was not removed by calling IPropertyContainer.remove(String). If no value was assigned (the key is unknown), a NoSuchPropertyException will be thrown.
        Specified by:
        get in interface IPropertyContainer
        Parameters:
        key - property name (case insensitive)
        Returns:
        value associated with key if set. If key is not known, throws NoSuchPropertyException.
        Throws:
        IPropertyContainer.NoSuchPropertyException
        See Also:
        IPropertyContainer.get(String, Object), IPropertyContainer.has(String), IPropertyContainer.remove(String)

      • has

        public boolean has(java.lang.String key)
        Description copied from interface: IPropertyContainer
        Checks if this object contains a property associated with the given key. Returns true if at some point earlier IPropertyContainer.set(String, Type, Object) was called with the corresponding key. Properties are stored persistently such that an assignment will be alive as long as it was not removed by calling IPropertyContainer.remove(String), and, hence, key will be alive. If no property is associated to key the method will return false.
        Specified by:
        has in interface IPropertyContainer
        Parameters:
        key - property name (case insensitive)
        Returns:
        true if the object contains a property associated to key, false otherwise.

        Returns a distinct collection of each assigned key for this object in (possible empty) set. Since keys are case-insensitive it depends on the implementation if the user-defined strings once passed as keys are changed in some way, e.g., by converting to lower case strings.

        public void remove(java.lang.String key)
            throws IPropertyContainer.NoSuchPropertyException
        Description copied from interface: IPropertyContainer
        Removes a per-object user-defined property identified by a custom key and value assigned by calling IPropertyContainer.set(String, Type, Object) earlier. Properties are stored persistently such that an assignment will be alive as long as it this method does not remove the property. If this object does not contain any property associated to key, a NoSuchPropertyException will be thrown.

      • set

        public <T> void set(java.lang.String key,
                    IPropertyContainer.Type type,
                    T value)
        Description copied from interface: IPropertyContainer
        Sets a per-object user-defined property consisting of a values associated with a user-defined key. If key is already set, the behavior of this method depends on the KeyConflictPolicy.

        Properties are stored persistently such that an assignment will be alive as long as it was not removed by calling IPropertyContainer.remove(String).

        To receive the value behind a key, call IPropertyContainer.get(String, Object).
        Specified by:
        set in interface IPropertyContainer
        Parameters:
        key - property name (case insensitive)
        type - type of value to be stored
        value - value to be stored
